<item>
            <title>[HBASE-8037] RegionMovedException is handled incorrectly for multi-region requests that fail completely</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-8037</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;RegionMovedException is currently thrown on global level, and due to how ProtobufUtil does things, it fails the entire multi-request, see &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-8036&quot; title=&quot;ProtobufUtil.multi behavior is inconsistent in case of errors&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-8036&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-8036&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. RME also doesn&apos;t specify the region.&lt;br/&gt;
Thus, if it&apos;s thrown for one region and there are multiple regions in the request, HCM applies it to all of them, which causes clients to become confused temporarily. We should either fix &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-8036&quot; title=&quot;ProtobufUtil.multi behavior is inconsistent in case of errors&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-8036&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-8036&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; or add region encoded name in the description. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12635951">HBASE-8037</key>
